<xs:schema xmlns:pvc="eu.3cixty.privacy" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" targetNamespace="eu.3cixty.privacy" elementFormDefault="qualified" attributeFormDefault="unqualified">
	<xs:element name="PrivacyContract">
		<xs:annotation>
			<xs:documentation>Contract proposal of an application using the privacy platform.
			This contract will be discussed with the privacy authority
			</xs:documentation>
		</xs:annotation>
		<xs:complexType>
			<xs:sequence>
				<xs:element name="application">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Information about the application that propose this contract</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
					<xs:complexType>
						<xs:sequence>
							<xs:element name="name" type="xs:string" nillable="false">
								<xs:annotation>
									<xs:documentation>How the application is known from the user</xs:documentation>
								</xs:annotation>
							</xs:element>
							<xs:element name="description" type="xs:string" nillable="false">
								<xs:annotation>
									<xs:documentation>Explanation of the services provided by the application</xs:documentation>
								</xs:annotation>
							</xs:element>
							<xs:element name="version" type="xs:string" nillable="false">
								<xs:annotation>
									<xs:documentation>Application version number</xs:documentation>
								</xs:annotation>
							</xs:element>
							<xs:element name="author" type="xs:string" nillable="false">
								<xs:annotation>
									<xs:documentation>Application provider : company, person...</xs:documentation>
								</xs:annotation>
							</xs:element>
							<xs:element name="domains">
								<xs:annotation>
									<xs:documentation>Categorization of the application services.

For example : 
- Transport if the application provides public transport itineraries
- Food if the application deals with restaurant reservation
- ....

An application could cover several domains.</xs:documentation>
								</xs:annotation>
								<xs:complexType>
									<xs:sequence maxOccurs="unbounded">
										<xs:element name="domain" type="pvc:Domain"/>
									</xs:sequence>
								</xs:complexType>
							</xs:element>
						</xs:sequence>
					</xs:complexType>
				</xs:element>
				<xs:sequence/>
				<xs:element name="contract">
					<xs:annotation>
						<xs:documentation>Defines the part of the user profile the application wants to access
The decription must be done with SPARQL property paths (a sequence of property names).

For non-SPARQL litterates, a textual description can be provided.
The privacy authority will contact you later to assist you in the the SPARQL property paths redaction.</xs:documentation>
					</xs:annotation>
					<xs:complexType>
						<xs:sequence>
							<xs:element name="namespaces" minOccurs="0">
								<xs:annotation>
									<xs:documentation>A sequence of abbreviated forms of namespace used in the propertyPaths elements</xs:documentation>
								</xs:annotation>
								<xs:complexType>
									<xs:sequence maxOccurs="unbounded">
										<xs:element name="namespace">
											<xs:annotation>
												<xs:documentation>Description of the namespace :
 - a prefix that is the abbreviated form
 - an uri that is the expanded form

Example:
 - prefix = profile
 - uri = http://3cixty.eurecom.fr/ontology/profile/</xs:documentation>
											</xs:annotation>
											<xs:complexType>
												<xs:sequence>
													<xs:element name="prefix" type="xs:string"/>
													<xs:element name="uri" type="xs:string"/>
												</xs:sequence>
											</xs:complexType>
										</xs:element>
									</xs:sequence>
								</xs:complexType>
							</xs:element>
							<xs:choice>
								<xs:element name="propertyPaths">
									<xs:annotation>
										<xs:documentation>A sequence of SPARQL property paths with a type attribute that specifies if the data is mandatory or optional to your service execution</xs:documentation>
									</xs:annotation>
									<xs:complexType>
										<xs:sequence maxOccurs="unbounded">
											<xs:element name="propertyPath">
												<xs:annotation>
													<xs:documentation>The SPARQL path to the value that the service wants to access.

Example with the profile.ttl :
 - An application that wants to access Tray elements must specify the following path:
     profile:trayElement 

 - An application that wants to access to the accountName in a Tray :
       
profile:trayElement/profile:hasAccount/foaf:accountName

pvc:type
 - 2 values available : optional or mandatory
 - the default value is the 'optional' value</xs:documentation>
												</xs:annotation>
												<xs:complexType>
													<xs:simpleContent>
														<xs:extension base="xs:string">
															<xs:attribute ref="pvc:type" use="optional" default="optional"/>
														</xs:extension>
													</xs:simpleContent>
												</xs:complexType>
											</xs:element>
										</xs:sequence>
									</xs:complexType>
								</xs:element>
								<xs:element name="textDescription" type="xs:string" nillable="false">
									<xs:annotation>
										<xs:documentation>Specify as accurately as possible, your required data</xs:documentation>
									</xs:annotation>
								</xs:element>
							</xs:choice>
						</xs:sequence>
					</xs:complexType>
				</xs:element>
			</xs:sequence>
			<xs:attribute name="schemaVersion" type="xs:string" use="required" fixed="1.0"/>
		</xs:complexType>
	</xs:element>
	<xs:attribute name="type">
		<xs:simpleType>
			<xs:restriction base="xs:string">
				<xs:enumeration value="mandatory"/>
				<xs:enumeration value="optional"/>
			</xs:restriction>
		</xs:simpleType>
	</xs:attribute>
	<xs:simpleType name="Domain">
		<xs:restriction base="xs:string">
			<xs:enumeration value="Food"/>
			<xs:enumeration value="Cultural"/>
			<xs:enumeration value="Health"/>
			<xs:enumeration value="Transport"/>
			<xs:enumeration value="Communication"/>
			<xs:enumeration value="Entertainment"/>
			<xs:enumeration value="Religion"/>
			<xs:enumeration value="Education"/>
			<xs:enumeration value="Financial"/>
			<xs:enumeration value="Other"/>
			<xs:enumeration value="Sport"/>
			<xs:enumeration value="Tourism"/>
		</xs:restriction>
	</xs:simpleType>
</xs:schema>
